3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">PATRONAE\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">E\u003C/span>T·UXORI·RARISS\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">C\u003C/span>\u003Cspan class=\"underline\">IUNIUS\u003C/span>MERCURIUS\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000034_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000034_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic000034.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana\" src=\"ISic000034-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Text of Mommsen\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"1\">1: \u003Cspan>Omitted by Gualtherus\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003Cbr>\u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"4\">4: \u003Cspan>Bivona: [---]Mercuṛ[iu]ṣ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Bivona essentially dismisses the earlier tradition (which, as per her practice throughout the catalogue, she does not report or reference), seemingly on the sole basis that she read F, not E, as the first surviving letter of line 2. Gualtherus saw the piece entire, and Mommsen the surviving right half, and there is no obvious reason to doubt Gualtherus' report of the original entire text.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u